- To install dJango
	pip install django
- Check if django installed:
	django-admin
	
- To start new project:
	django admin startproject <project_name>
	
- To run django project:
	python manage.py runserver
	
- To add new app in django project:
	python manage.py startapp <app_name>
	
	- after creating app, register it in settings.py > INSTALLED_APPS > [] > add app name here

- To add static files, create a folder for hosting static files e.g. styling, images and javascript in project root directory
	- Add the folder name to the settings.py as
		STATICFILES_DIRS = [
		    os.path.join(BASE_DIR, '<static_folder_name>')
		]
	- To add images, declare the images base path in settings.py
		MEDIA_URL = '/images/'

- To use static files in templates, use {% load static %} on top of the file, 
	- and then call the static files any where in template by using 
		{% static '/<path inside the static directory>/filename.css' %}

- To run migrations:
	python manage.py migrate

- To generate new migrations:
	python manage.py makemigrations

- To create django super user:
	python manage.py createsuperuser

- To get the model displayed and interact with it in django admin panel, import the model into admin.py and register it as:
	admin.site.register(<Model>)

- To run django shell
	python manage.py shell
	- here we can run database queries or run the python code
	- for making query, we need to import necessary models inside shell

- To add URL parameter, add <str:param_name> in URL. e.g. /customers/<str:id>
	- Then access this URL param in views function by adding function parameter with the same name

- We can add names in URLs, which can be used for in-app routing
	- adding name in url:
		path('', views.home, name="home"),
	- For in app routing through template:
		<a  href="{% url 'home' %}">Dashboard </a>